        <name>
            <text>11.2.1.1 Table of derivatives</text>
        </name>
        <questiontext format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
<h4>
    <span class="multilang" lang="en">
        Table of derivatives
    </span>
    <span class="multilang" lang="no">
        Tabell over derivativer
    </span>
</h4>
<p>
    <span class="multilang" lang="en">
        The table below lists some of the common functions used in engineering and their corresponding derivatives. Remember that in each case the function in the right-hand column gives the rate of change, or the gradient of the graph, of the function on the left at a particular value of \(x\).
N.B. The angle must always be in radians when differentiating trigonometric functions.
    </span>
    <span class="multilang" lang="no">
        Tabellen under lister opp noen av de vanlige funksjonene som brukes i ingeni&#248;rfag og deres tilh&#248;rende derivater. Husk at i hvert tilfelle gir funksjonen i h&#248;yre kolonne endringstakten, eller stigningen til grafen, av funksjonen til venstre p&#229; en bestemt verdi av \(x\).
Obs. Vinkelen m&#229; alltid v&#230;re i radianer n&#229;r man deriverer trigonometriske funksjoner.
    </span>
</p>
<table class="HELM_table">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>
                <p>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                        Function
                    </span>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                        Funksjon
                    </span>
                </p>
            </th>
            <th>
                <p>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                        Derivative
                    </span>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                        Den deriverte.
                    </span>
                </p>
            </th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <p>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                        constant
                    </span>
                    <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                        konstant
                    </span>
                </p>
            </td>
            <td>
                0
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                \(x\)
            </td>
            <td>
                \(1\)
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                \(kx\)
            </td>
            <td>
                \(k\)
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
